<text top="80" left="607" width="205" height="16" font="1">[Friday, 13 December 2013 </text>
<text top="1197" left="364" width="447" height="11" font="2">INTERNAL QUESTION PAPER: NATIONAL COUNCIL OF PROVINCES NO 37─2013 </text>
<text top="119" left="85" width="36" height="16" font="4"><b>152. </b></text>
<text top="119" left="139" width="600" height="16" font="4"><b>Mr D A Worth (DA-FS) to ask the Minister of Defence and Military Veterans:</b></text>
<text top="119" left="739" width="5" height="16" font="1"> </text>
<text top="160" left="139" width="28" height="16" font="1">(1) </text>
<text top="160" left="193" width="622" height="16" font="1">(a) When was the last time the SA National Defence Force issued tenders for the </text>
<text top="181" left="193" width="625" height="16" font="1">maintenance and repair of its vehicles and (b) which companies are currently </text>
<text top="201" left="193" width="481" height="16" font="1">involved with the maintenance and repair of the SANDF vehicles; </text>
<text top="243" left="139" width="28" height="16" font="1">(2) </text>
<text top="243" left="193" width="622" height="16" font="1">whether all companies that are involved have been appointed through a thorough </text>
<text top="264" left="193" width="620" height="16" font="1">tender process; if not, why not; if so, what are the details of the processes that have </text>
<text top="285" left="193" width="112" height="16" font="1">been followed; </text>
<text top="326" left="139" width="27" height="16" font="1">(3) </text>
<text top="326" left="193" width="621" height="16" font="1">what was the total amount that was paid to the companies that were involved with </text>
<text top="347" left="193" width="592" height="16" font="1">the maintenance and repair of the SANDF vehicles in the 2012-13 financial year? </text>
<text top="347" left="808" width="5" height="16" font="1"> </text>
<text top="365" left="193" width="5" height="16" font="1"> </text>
<text top="367" left="752" width="60" height="13" font="13">CW246E </text>
<text top="407" left="336" width="226" height="19" font="10"><b>FRIDAY, 14 JUNE 2013 </b></text>
<text top="452" left="85" width="36" height="16" font="4"><b>254. </b></text>
<text top="452" left="139" width="663" height="16" font="4"><b>Mr R A Lees (DA-KZN) to ask the Minister of Rural Development and Land Reform: </b></text>
<text top="493" left="139" width="26" height="16" font="1">(1) </text>
<text top="493" left="193" width="620" height="16" font="1">With reference to his reply to Question 133 on 28 May 2013, (a) what are the details </text>
<text top="513" left="193" width="622" height="16" font="1">of each beneficiary who (i) has benefited or (ii) will benefit from the purchase of </text>
<text top="534" left="193" width="621" height="16" font="1">each portion of land by a certain company (name furnished) and (b) on what basis </text>
<text top="555" left="193" width="232" height="16" font="1">are these beneficiaries selected; </text>
<text top="597" left="139" width="26" height="16" font="1">(2) </text>
<text top="597" left="193" width="620" height="16" font="1">whether these beneficiaries are (a) members or (b) stakeholders of the said company; </text>
<text top="617" left="193" width="549" height="16" font="1">if not, what is the position in this regard; if so, what are the relevant details; </text>
<text top="659" left="139" width="27" height="16" font="1">(3) </text>
<text top="659" left="193" width="620" height="16" font="1">(a) what are the details of each director of the said company and (b) who are the (i) </text>
<text top="680" left="193" width="377" height="16" font="1">members and (ii) stakeholders of the said company; </text>
<text top="721" left="139" width="29" height="16" font="1">(4) </text>
<text top="721" left="193" width="623" height="16" font="1">whether any additional funds other than for the purchase of the land have been </text>
<text top="742" left="193" width="620" height="16" font="1">and/or will be made available directly or indirectly by the State to the said company; </text>
<text top="763" left="193" width="619" height="16" font="1">if not, what is the position in this regard; if so, (a) what are the details of the funds in </text>
<text top="783" left="193" width="438" height="16" font="1">each case and (b) for what purpose will these funds be used; </text>
<text top="825" left="139" width="27" height="16" font="1">(5) </text>
<text top="825" left="193" width="621" height="16" font="1">whether the use of these funds will be audited; if not, why not; if so, what are the </text>
<text top="846" left="193" width="122" height="16" font="1">relevant details? </text>
<text top="848" left="752" width="56" height="13" font="13">CW351E</text>
<text top="846" left="808" width="5" height="16" font="1"> </text>
<text top="889" left="325" width="248" height="19" font="10"><b>FRIDAY, 2 AUGUST 2013 </b></text>
<text top="933" left="85" width="36" height="16" font="4"><b>285. </b></text>
<text top="933" left="139" width="600" height="16" font="4"><b>Mr D A Worth (DA-FS) to ask the Minister of Defence and Military Veterans:</b></text>
<text top="933" left="739" width="5" height="16" font="1"> </text>
<text top="974" left="139" width="673" height="16" font="1">Whether her departmental officials are undergoing any fitness tests; if not, why not; if so, (a) </text>
<text top="995" left="139" width="674" height="16" font="1">how frequent are these tests done and (b) how many officials failed (i) to undergo the tests </text>
<text top="1016" left="139" width="533" height="16" font="1">in the 2012-13 financial year and (ii) their tests in the said financial year? </text>
<text top="1018" left="752" width="56" height="13" font="13">CW383E</text>
<text top="1016" left="808" width="5" height="16" font="1"> </text>
<text top="1059" left="139" width="5" height="19" font="10"><b> </b></text>
<text top="1059" left="355" width="5" height="19" font="10"><b> </b></text>
</page>
